genresAdvancedInfo.name: atlanta bass
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Atlanta bass is a subgenre of hip hop that originated in Atlanta, Georgia in the early 2000s. It is characterized by heavy basslines, trap-style beats, and lyrics that often focus on materialism, drug use, and street life. Atlanta bass has become one of the most popular subgenres of hip hop in recent years, with artists like Future, Migos, and Lil Baby leading the way.
